body.p:
The contextual menu is available when clicking the current editor tab label. It shows the
      following actions:

Close - closes the current editor;

Close Other Files - closes all opened editor but the one you are
          currently viewing;

Close All - closes all opened editors;

Reopen last closed editor - reopens the last closed editor;

Maximize/Restore Editor Area - collapses all the side views and
          spans the editing are to cover the entire width of the main window;

Add to project - adds the file you are editing to the current
          project;

Add all to project - adds all the opened files to the current
          project;

Copy Location - copies the disk location of the file;

Show in Explorer (Show in Finder on OS X) - opens the Explorer to
          the file path of the file.
